VALUES('28844ae6-d482-441b-abd6-09db2a64c707', 'DevOps Engineer', 'netflix', 'https://netflix.com/jobs', '<h3>Company Description</h3><p>Netflix is the world&apos;s leading streaming entertainment service with over 260 million paid memberships in over 190 countries enjoying TV series, documentaries, and feature films across a wide variety of genres and languages. At Netflix, we push the boundaries of storytelling and technology, enabling content creators and engineers to deliver seamless and scalable user experiences worldwide.</p><h3>Job Description</h3><p>As a DevOps Engineer at Netflix, you will be an integral part of the platform engineering team responsible for building and maintaining the infrastructure and deployment pipelines that power Netflix&apos;s global streaming platform. You&apos;ll collaborate with developers, SREs, and security engineers to automate and optimize every stage of the software delivery lifecycle.</p><p>This role is ideal for an engineer who thrives in a fast-paced, highly collaborative environment and is passionate about infrastructure as code, automation, and reliability at scale.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Design, implement, and maintain scalable CI/CD pipelines for deploying microservices and applications.</li><li>Automate provisioning and configuration of cloud infrastructure using tools like Terraform and Spinnaker.</li><li>Enhance monitoring and alerting systems to ensure high availability and performance of services.</li><li>Collaborate with development teams to improve build and release processes.</li><li>Implement security best practices throughout the DevOps lifecycle.</li><li>Continuously improve system reliability through post-incident reviews and proactive analysis.</li></ul><h3>Qualifications</h3><ul><li>Bachelor&apos;s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience.</li><li>3+ years of experience in DevOps, SRE, or infrastructure engineering roles.</li><li>Strong experience with cloud platforms such as AWS or GCP.</li><li>Expertise in containerization technologies like Docker and orchestration tools like Kubernetes.</li><li>Proficiency with infrastructure-as-code tools (Terraform, CloudFormation, etc.).</li><li>Experience with CI/CD tools (e.g., Jenkins, Spinnaker, GitHub Actions).</li><li>Strong scripting skills in Python, Bash, or Go.</li><li>Deep understanding of monitoring, logging, and alerting systems such as Prometheus, Grafana, ELK, or Datadog.</li><li>Excellent troubleshooting skills and a proactive mindset.</li></ul><h3>Preferred Qualifications</h3><ul><li>Experience working in high-scale production environments.</li><li>Knowledge of Netflix OSS tools is a plus (e.g., Spinnaker, Chaos Monkey).</li><li>Understanding of zero-downtime deployment strategies and disaster recovery planning.</li></ul><h3>Additional Information</h3><p>The typical base pay range for this role is $130,000 - $200,000 USD, plus equity and comprehensive benefits.</p><p>Compensation is determined by role level, skills, and experience. Netflix provides a unique culture that values freedom and responsibility. We empower employees to make decisions and innovate boldly. Learn more about our culture at <a href=&quot;https://jobs.netflix.com/culture&quot;>https://jobs.netflix.com/culture</a>.</p><p>Netflix is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees.</p>',      449440,  '0-3', 'los gatos', 'united states (us)', 'remote', '2025-04-30 11:16:06.174262', '2025-04-30 11:16:06.174262'),

('84576c8c-9e88-494d-bdd9-e855247e11df', 'Software Engineer - I', 'microsoft', 'https://microsoft.com/careers', '<h3>Company Description</h3><p>Microsoft is a global leader in technology, empowering every person and every organization on the planet to achieve more. With a mission to build best-in-class platforms and productivity services for an intelligent cloud and an intelligent edge, Microsoft develops innovative solutions to serve millions of customers around the globe.</p><p>At Microsoft, we believe in a growth mindset, collaboration, and the power of diverse perspectives. We are committed to providing a supportive and inclusive environment where early-career engineers can learn, grow, and contribute meaningfully from day one.</p><h3>Job Description</h3><p>As a Software Engineer I at Microsoft, you will join a world-class engineering team that builds critical products and services used by billions of people worldwide. You will work on real projects that have broad customer impact, collaborate with experienced mentors and peers, and contribute to software development, testing, and maintenance across various Microsoft product lines.</p><p>This entry-level role is ideal for early career engineers passionate about building reliable, scalable, and innovative solutions using cutting-edge technologies.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Design, develop, and maintain software solutions in collaboration with cross-functional teams.</li><li>Participate in code reviews, debugging, and troubleshooting to ensure high-quality code.</li><li>Work with product managers and designers to define and implement user-centric features.</li><li>Contribute to technical documentation, testing, and continuous integration pipelines.</li><li>Continuously learn and stay up-to-date with emerging technologies and engineering practices.</li></ul><h3>Qualifications</h3><ul><li>Bachelor&apos;s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field (or currently pursuing with