('e58056e6-28e1-43de-afda-8c6e9363ddda', 'Backend Developer', 'openai', 'https://openai.com/jobs', '<h3>Company Description</h3><p>OpenAI is a research organization and technology company that focuses on developing artificial general intelligence (AGI) that benefits all of humanity. Our mission is to ensure that AGI is developed safely and its benefits are widely distributed. We are driven by the belief that artificial intelligence should be an essential tool for advancing science, solving real-world problems, and improving quality of life.</p><p>At OpenAI, we work at the forefront of AI research and engineering, combining deep technical expertise with a commitment to safety, ethics, and inclusivity. Join us as we shape the future of artificial intelligence.</p><h3>Job Description</h3><p>As a Backend Developer at OpenAI, you will play a key role in building and scaling backend systems that power our AI products and services. You will work on mission-critical systems that support our machine learning models, ensuring reliability, performance, and scalability across a wide range of products.</p><p>You will work alongside top-tier engineers and researchers to design and implement robust, scalable backend services that enable the deployment of cutting-edge AI technologies.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Design, implement, and maintain backend services and APIs that support OpenAIs products and research initiatives.</li><li>Work on optimizing and scaling backend systems to handle large-scale data processing and model inference.</li><li>Collaborate with machine learning engineers and researchers to integrate AI models into production systems.</li><li>Ensure high availability, reliability, and performance of backend systems while following best practices for distributed systems.</li><li>Write clean, maintainable, and efficient code while adhering to industry standards.</li><li>Participate in code reviews, debugging, and troubleshooting, ensuring quality across the backend stack.</li></ul><h3>Qualifications</h3><ul><li>Bachelors or Masters degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience.</li><li>3+ years of experience in backend development, with proficiency in at least one of the following languages: Python, Go, Java, or C++.</li><li>Experience with building and maintaining scalable, distributed systems using cloud platforms like AWS, GCP, or Azure.</li><li>Familiarity with RESTful APIs, microservices architecture, and containerization (e.g., Docker, Kubernetes).</li><li>Strong understanding of data structures, algorithms, and system design principles.</li><li>Experience with relational and NoSQL databases (e.g., PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Redis).</li><li>Ability to work effectively in a collaborative, fast-paced environment.</li></ul><h3>Preferred Qualifications</h3><ul><li>Experience with machine learning and deep learning frameworks (e.g., TensorFlow, PyTorch) and integrating models into production systems.</li><li>Familiarity with message queues and streaming technologies (e.g., Kafka, RabbitMQ).</li><li>Knowledge of continuous integration and deployment (CI/CD) processes and tools.</li></ul><h3>Additional Information</h3><p>The base salary range for this role is $140,000 to $200,000 USD annually, with additional compensation through equity, performance bonuses, and a comprehensive benefits package.</p><p>OpenAI is an equal opportunity employer. We are committed to fostering an inclusive environment and encourage applicants from all backgrounds to apply. We do not discriminate based on race, color, religion, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, age, disability, or veteran status.</p><p>To learn more and apply, visit <a href=https://openai.com/careers>https://openai.com/careers</a>.</p>', 278798, '0-3', 'san francisco', 'united states (us)', 'remote',  '2025-04-30 11:16:06.174262', '2025-04-30 11:16:06.174262'),

('3a9a2ae4-432e-4c4b-924e-7e96cb2125a6',    'Software Engineer - II',  'google',  'https://google.com',      '<h3>Company Description</h3><p>Google&apos;s mission is to organize the world&apos;s information and make it universally accessible and useful. Our teams are constantly solving some of the world&apos;s most challenging and impactful engineering problems. As a company, we embrace innovation and collaboration to make products that impact billions of users every day.</p><h3>Job Description</h3><p>As a Software Engineer II at Google, you will work on a team with highly motivated engineers developing scalable, reliable, and maintainable software systems. You&apos;ll collaborate across various disciplines including Product Management, UX, and other Engineering teams to bring new ideas to life and continuously improve existing applications.</p><p>You will write and maintain code, participate in code reviews, and provide feedback on best practices in software development. You&apos;ll also analyze complex technical challenges and devise solutions that align with Google&apos;s infrastructure and product goals.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Design, develop, test, deploy, maintain, and improve software and services.</li><li>Participate in architecture and design discussions across multiple systems.</li><li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams to define and implement new features.</li><li>Write clean, maintainable code with unit and integration tests.</li><li>Troubleshoot and resolve issues across the software stack.</li><li>Mentor junior engineers and share best practices.</li></ul><h3>Qualifications</h3><ul><li>Bachelor&apos;s degree or equivalent practical experience in Computer Science or related field.</li><li>2-4 years of industry experience in software development.</li><li>Experience with one or more programming languages such as Java, C++, Python, or Go.</li><li>Solid understanding of algorithms, data structures, and software design principles.</li><li>Working knowledge of APIs, databases, and backend systems.</li><li>Excellent problem-solving and communication skills.</li></ul><h3>Preferred Qualifications</h3><ul><li>Experience working on large-scale distributed systems.</li><li>Familiarity with Google Cloud Platform (GCP) or other cloud environments.</li><li>Ability to adapt quickly to changing requirements and technologies.</li><li>Enthusiasm for continuous learning and knowledge sharing.</li></ul><h3>Additional Information</h3><p>The US base salary range for this full-time position is $115,000 to $160,000 + bonus + equity + benefits.</p><p>Salary ranges are determined by role, level, and location. They are subject to change and may vary depending on individual qualifications and experience. Google is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. We are committed to building a diverse and inclusive workplace, and we encourage all qualified applicants to apply regardless of race, color, religion, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, age, disability status, or veteran status.</p><p><a href=&quot;https://careers.google.com&quot;>Learn more about Google careers here</a>.</p>',   526233,  '3-5',     'bengaluru',       'india',   'full_time',      '2025-04-30 11:16:06.174262', '2025-04-30 11:16:06.174262'),

('404784eb-ba77-4f60-94ea-4a170be9fd7e',    'Backend Developer',       'atlassian',       'https://atlassian.com/careers',   '<h3>Company Description</h3><p>Atlassian unleashes the potential of every team. Our collaboration and productivity software helps teams organize, discuss, and complete shared work. Millions of users across small businesses, startups, and large enterprises-including teams at NASA, Twitter, and Deloitte-rely on our products like Jira, Confluence, Bitbucket, and Trello to accelerate innovation and drive business success.</p><p>We&apos;re a distributed-first company, meaning you can work from almost anywhere. At Atlassian, you&apos;ll join a team that values openness, autonomy, and continuous learning, while solving meaningful technical challenges with global impact.</p><h3>Job Description</h3><p>As a Backend Engineer at Atlassian, you will be a key contributor to the design, development, and optimization of backend systems that scale to serve millions of users. You&apos;ll work in an agile environment, closely collaborating with cross-functional teams to build and ship high-quality features and services for our cloud-based products.</p><p>If you are passionate about performance, reliability, clean architecture, and delivering value through code, this role is for you.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Design and implement backend components and services using modern languages and frameworks (Java, Kotlin, Spring Boot, etc.).</li><li>Write clean, scalable, and well-tested code that meets business and technical requirements.</li><li>Contribute to system architecture discussions and decisions.</li><li>Collaborate with frontend developers, designers, and product managers to define APIs and deliver seamless user experiences.</li><li>Monitor, maintain, and improve performance and reliability of production systems.</li><li>Participate in code reviews, testing, and deployment pipelines in a CI/CD environment.</li></ul><h3>Qualifications</h3><ul><li>Bachelor&apos;s or Master&apos;s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience.</li><li>2+ years of professional experience in backend software development.</li><li>Proficiency in one or more server-side languages such as Java, Kotlin, or Node.js.</li><li>Experience with relational and NoSQL databases (e.g., PostgreSQL, DynamoDB, Redis).</li><li>Understanding of cloud-native architecture and familiarity with AWS, GCP, or Azure.</li><li>Strong problem-solving skills, debugging capabilities, and attention to detail.</li></ul><h3>Preferred Qualifications</h3><ul><li>Experience with microservices, distributed systems, or large-scale SaaS applications.</li><li>Familiarity with Atlassian products like Jira or Confluence is a plus.</li><li>Knowledge of containerization technologies such as Docker and Kubernetes.</li></ul><h3>Additional Information</h3><p>The base pay range for this role is $120,000 to $155,000 USD annually, along with equity, performance bonuses, and comprehensive benefits.</p><p>Atlassian is an equal opportunity employer and is committed to diversity and inclusion. We encourage candidates from all backgrounds to apply. Learn more about life at Atlassian and explore our open roles at <a href=&quot;https://www.atlassian.com/company/careers&quot;>https://www.atlassian.com/company/careers</a>.</p>',  577699,  '0-1',     'sydney',  'australia',       'full_time',       '2025-04-30 11:16:06.174262', '2025-04-30 11:16:06.174262'),



('1106b297-4407-49bf-b233-b5636fb96851',    'Full Stack Developer',    'meta',    'https://facebook.com/careers',    '<h3>Company Description</h3><p>Meta builds technologies that help people connect, find communities, and grow businesses. With apps like Facebook, Instagram, WhatsApp, and Threads, Meta is redefining how people around the world interact and share. Behind these products are teams of skilled engineers tackling some of the world&apos;s most complex and impactful technical challenges.</p><p>At Meta, we embrace a culture of curiosity, continuous learning, and bold innovation. Join us in building the future of social technologies.</p><h3>Job Description</h3><p>As a Full Stack Engineer at Meta, you will be responsible for designing, developing, and maintaining end-to-end features across the stack - from backend systems to frontend interfaces. You&apos;ll collaborate with product managers, designers, and engineers to create scalable, reliable, and user-centric web experiences across Meta&apos;s family of applications.</p><p>You will work on systems that support billions of users, using cutting-edge technologies to solve complex problems in performance, privacy, and infrastructure.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Design, build, and maintain full stack applications using modern frameworks such as React, Node.js, and GraphQL.</li><li>Implement backend services, APIs, and data models to support frontend experiences.</li><li>Optimize application performance, reliability, and scalability.</li><li>Collaborate cross-functionally with design, product, and data teams to define and deliver product features.</li><li>Participate in code reviews, testing, and continuous integration/deployment workflows.</li><li>Contribute to engineering best practices and mentor junior developers.</li></ul><h3>Qualifications</h3><ul><li>Bachelor&apos;s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience.</li><li>2+ years of experience developing full stack web applications in a production environment.</li><li>Proficiency in JavaScript/TypeScript and frontend frameworks such as React or Next.js.</li><li>Experience with server-side technologies such as Node.js, Python, PHP, or Go.</li><li>Strong understanding of databases (SQL and NoSQL), data modeling, and REST/GraphQL APIs.</li><li>Knowledge of version control systems (e.g., Git) and CI/CD pipelines.</li></ul><h3>Preferred Qualifications</h3><ul><li>Experience working with large-scale distributed systems or cloud platforms (e.g., AWS, GCP).</li><li>Familiarity with Meta&apos;s technologies or open source projects (e.g., React, Relay, PyTorch).</li><li>Understanding of data privacy, security, and accessibility principles.</li></ul><h3>Additional Information</h3><p>The base salary range for this role is $125,000 to $170,000 USD annually, with additional compensation through bonuses, equity, and comprehensive benefits including wellness programs, parental leave, and professional development resources.</p><p>Meta is proud to be an equal opportunity and affirmative action employer. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, gender identity, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status.</p><p>Learn more and apply at <a href=&quot;https://www.metacareers.com&quot;>https://www.metacareers.com</a>.</p>', 118518,  '5+',      'hyderabad',      'india',   'full_time',       '2025-04-30 11:16:06.174262', '2025-04-30 11:16:06.174262'),



