('af2742da-95ef-4629-b189-2ec59ce24f90',    'ML Engineer',     'google',  'https://google.com/careers',      '<h3>Company Description</h3><p>Google is a global leader in technology, known for its mission to organize the worlds information and make it universally accessible and useful. With innovations in search, cloud computing, advertising, and AI, Google serves billions of users around the world. At Google, we believe in using technology to solve the biggest challenges and improve everyday lives through cutting-edge machine learning and artificial intelligence.</p><h3>Job Description</h3><p>As a Machine Learning Engineer at Google Singapore, you will be part of a high-impact engineering team building intelligent systems that power products like Search, Google Assistant, YouTube, and Cloud AI. You will collaborate with researchers, software engineers, and product managers to design and deploy scalable ML solutions that operate at global scale and deliver exceptional user experiences.</p><p>This role is ideal for engineers with a strong background in machine learning and software development who are passionate about innovation, scalability, and responsible AI.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Design and implement scalable machine learning models and algorithms for real-world applications.</li><li>Work closely with cross-functional teams to understand product requirements and translate them into ML solutions.</li><li>Build and optimize data pipelines for training and inference at scale.</li><li>Deploy machine learning models to production and monitor their performance and accuracy.</li><li>Contribute to the development of internal tools and frameworks that streamline the ML lifecycle.</li><li>Ensure ethical and responsible AI practices are embedded in model development and deployment.</li><li>Stay updated with the latest advancements in machine learning research and apply them to solve business problems.</li></ul><h3>Qualifications</h3><ul><li>Bachelors or Masters degree in Computer Science, Machine Learning, Statistics, or a related technical field, or equivalent practical experience.</li><li>0-1 years of experience building machine learning models and deploying them in production environments.</li><li>Proficiency in Python or Java and ML libraries such as TensorFlow, PyTorch, or JAX.</li><li>Experience working with structured and unstructured data at scale.</li><li>Strong software engineering skills and experience with version control, testing, and CI/CD.</li><li>Knowledge of cloud platforms such as Google Cloud Platform, AWS, or Azure.</li><li>Understanding of data privacy, model fairness, and interpretability principles.</li><li>Excellent problem-solving and communication skills.</li></ul><h3>Preferred Qualifications</h3><ul><li>Experience in large-scale machine learning systems or recommendation engines.</li><li>Publications in top-tier ML conferences or open-source contributions.</li><li>Experience with AutoML, federated learning, or model compression techniques.</li></ul><h3>Additional Information</h3><p>This is a full-time position based in Singapore. Google offers competitive compensation, equity, and a comprehensive benefits package. At Google, we foster an inclusive and collaborative environment where innovation thrives. Learn more about working at Google at <a href=https://careers.google.com>https://careers.google.com</a>.</p><p>Google is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to building an inclusive workplace for all employees.</p>',  458548,  '0-1',     'one-north',       'singapore',       'full_time',      '2025-04-30 11:16:06.174262', '2025-04-30 11:16:06.174262'),

('1501120c-5f2e-4c83-9de3-01be35edbb5f',    'Data Engineer',   'microsoft',       'https://microsoft.com/careers',   '<h3>Company Description</h3><p>Microsoft is a global technology company that empowers every person and every organization on the planet to achieve more. With a strong presence in cloud computing, artificial intelligence, productivity software, and developer tools, Microsoft builds platforms and services that transform the way people live and work. Our teams innovate with purpose, aiming to build a more inclusive, secure, and sustainable world through technology.</p><h3>Job Description</h3><p>As a Data Engineer at Microsoft Singapore, you will be part of a dynamic and collaborative team working on the design, development, and optimization of data solutions that support business intelligence, analytics, and machine learning initiatives. This role offers a unique opportunity for early-career engineers to gain hands-on experience with modern data engineering tools and cloud technologies while contributing to impactful projects across various domains.</p><p>This role is ideal for recent graduates or early-career professionals who are passionate about data, eager to learn, and excited to grow within a supportive, fast-paced environment.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Design and build reliable and scalable data pipelines using tools such as Azure Data Factory, Databricks, or Apache Spark.</li><li>Ingest, transform, and organize large volumes of structured and unstructured data for analytics and reporting.</li><li>Collaborate with data scientists, analysts, and software engineers to understand data needs and deliver high-quality datasets.</li><li>Implement data validation, quality checks, and performance optimization across the data stack.</li><li>Develop and maintain documentation for data pipelines, processes, and schemas.</li><li>Participate in agile development practices including sprint planning, code reviews, and peer learning sessions.</li></ul><h3>Qualifications</h3><ul><li>Bachelors degree in Computer Science, Data Engineering, Information Systems, or a related field.</li><li>0 to 1 year of experience in data engineering, software development, or related internship/project experience.</li><li>Proficiency in SQL and basic understanding of scripting languages such as Python or Scala.</li><li>Familiarity with data modeling, ETL processes, and relational or NoSQL databases.</li><li>Exposure to cloud platforms such as Microsoft Azure, AWS, or GCP is a plus.</li><li>Strong problem-solving skills and eagerness to learn new technologies.</li><li>Excellent communication skills and ability to work in a team environment.</li></ul><h3>Preferred Qualifications</h3><ul><li>Coursework or project experience with big data technologies such as Spark, Hadoop, or Kafka.</li><li>Familiarity with Azure Synapse, Power BI, or other modern analytics platforms.</li><li>Participation in data engineering competitions, research, or open-source contributions is a plus.</li></ul><h3>Additional Information</h3><p>This is a full-time early career position based in Singapore. Microsoft offers a competitive salary, benefits, and career development opportunities. Our inclusive culture encourages innovation, collaboration, and personal growth. Learn more about our mission and values at <a href=https://careers.microsoft.com>https://careers.microsoft.com</a>.</p><p>Microsoft is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees.</p>',       701302, '0-1',     'one-north',      'singapore',       'full_time',      '2025-04-30 11:16:06.174262', '2025-04-30 11:16:06.174262'),

('af188a46-236a-40e5-8186-edcdf6e34d9b',    'Prompt Engineer', 'openai',  'https://openai.com/careers',      '<h3>Company Description</h3><p>OpenAI is an AI research and deployment company dedicated to ensuring that artificial general intelligence benefits all of humanity. Our mission is to build safe and broadly beneficial AI systems. We develop cutting-edge models like ChatGPT, DALL-E, and Codex, and collaborate with partners across the world to bring these technologies to real-world applications. At OpenAI, we value safety, transparency, and innovation, and we are committed to advancing AI responsibly.</p><h3>Job Description</h3><p>As a Prompt Engineer at OpenAI Tel Aviv, you will work at the intersection of language, machine learning, and product development. Your work will involve designing, testing, and optimizing prompts to guide large language models in generating accurate, relevant, and safe outputs across a wide range of use cases. You will collaborate with research scientists, product managers, and developers to improve model performance and unlock new AI capabilities.</p><p>This role is ideal for individuals who have strong analytical thinking, creativity, and a passion for working closely with state-of-the-art language models to push the boundaries of human-AI interaction.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Design and iterate on high-quality prompts for various tasks including question answering, summarization, content generation, and coding assistance.</li><li>Evaluate model outputs for accuracy, relevance, and safety, and refine prompt structures accordingly.</li><li>Collaborate with research and engineering teams to identify prompt strategies that improve model alignment and usability.</li><li>Develop scalable prompt testing and evaluation workflows using internal tools and frameworks.</li><li>Contribute to prompt engineering best practices, templates, and internal documentation.</li><li>Analyze prompt behavior across model versions and edge cases to inform future training and product development.</li><li>Stay informed about the latest developments in LLMs and prompt tuning techniques.</li></ul><h3>Qualifications</h3><ul><li>Bachelors or Masters degree in Computer Science, Linguistics, Cognitive Science, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience.</li><li>2 to 3 years of experience in working with NLP systems, machine learning applications, or prompt engineering.</li><li>Strong proficiency in English and a deep understanding of language structure and usage.</li><li>Experience working with LLM APIs such as GPT, Claude, or PaLM is highly desirable.</li><li>Ability to think creatively, iterate quickly, and communicate insights clearly.</li><li>Basic scripting or programming experience with Python or JavaScript.</li><li>Comfort with ambiguity, experimentation, and a fast-paced development cycle.</li></ul><h3>Preferred Qualifications</h3><ul><li>Experience with prompt tuning, fine-tuning, or few-shot learning techniques.</li><li>Familiarity with safety and alignment challenges in large language models.</li><li>Background in UX writing, technical writing, or conversational design is a plus.</li></ul><h3>Additional Information</h3><p>This is a full-time position based in Tel Aviv, Israel. Compensation includes competitive salary, equity, and benefits. At OpenAI, we foster a culture of curiosity, autonomy, and mission-driven impact. Learn more about our work and values at <a href=https://openai.com/careers>https://openai.com/careers</a>.</p><p>OpenAI is an equal opportunity employer. We are committed to building a diverse and inclusive team and encourage applications from all qualified individuals.</p>',    640478,  '2-3',     'tel-aviv',        'israel',  'remote',  '2025-04-30 11:16:06.174262', '2025-04-30 11:16:06.174262');
